<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-03-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-05T06:00:00-05:00" n="661" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d661">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                        </head>
                        <p>On April 3, 1952, the Paraguayan Government made a payment of $34,372.82
                            to the United States Treasury in final settlement of obligations
                            incurred under the Lend-Lease Agreement of September 20, 1941
                            (734.56/4–352). For text of the Agreement, see <ref target="frus1941v07#pg_480">
                                <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1941, volume VII, page
                                480</ref>.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>